Description: Two fragments of a jar-seal: of pale brown clay, with remains of a seal impression of Khasekhem.. The surface of the clay is worn and cracked.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' II, pl.XXIV, 202 or 204; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.83, abb.311 or 312; see also vols. I, 161 and II, 854, n.978; 1135-6.
